    "type": "message",
    "text": "Really interesting paper, though a lot of the category theory was hard to decipher for me. \nI love hypergraph rewriting systems! The flexibility of hypergraph structures, along with their ability to easily represent higher-order structure is great. \n\nThey're portable between models of computation, can represent semantics, and express structure. They also happen to be incredibly simple.\nI think that makes hypergraphs (and their mathematical siblings) an _incredibly_ compelling primitive.",
