  {
    "client_msg_id": "b8ba7390-b2df-4484-9303-5665f718da82",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I came across Future Of Coding while doing a random search on the Internet for Alan Kay fans! Thank you <@U5TCAFTD3> and <@UC2A2ARPT> for this community! I’m an imagineer and protocol designer and believe also that the computer revolution has not happened yet. I’m this guy: <https://awake.vc/amit>\n\nI’m here to indulge my first loves: functional programming, distributed computing, new abstractions, smart people, early-stage startups, alien tech. I would love to contribute in various ways to cool projects I’m sure you all have. I also have a couple of new side projects I’m looking to find kindred spirits for, one has to do with a better software stack for modern Internet applications, and the other is a new Tangle-type abstraction for shared secrets.\n\nOh, in what seems like a past life, I wrote Clojure in Action (<https://awake.to/clojure>).",
